1. Explain what the terminal is in your own words.
	In my own words, a terminal is a control center on a computer that you can use to create, delete, move and control different platforms, files, or documents.

2. What is the major difference between Git and GitHub?
	The major difference between Git & GitHub is that Git is used in a terminal as a control system & GitHub is a platform that uses Git to complete certain tasks, but not just terminal tasks.

3.  What are the steps to fork a GitHub repository?
	1. Go to a repository on GitHub that isn't your own
	2. Click the Fork button on the top right of the page
	3. A new page appears. You can change the Repo name if you like. Afterwards, click the "Create fork" button.

	You should have the repo you forked in your GitHub account.